The paper deals with graph packing problems, which are often studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of trees and cycles suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.GT). Finally, the study of 1-planar graphs, which are a special type of graph drawing, may also be relevant to computer graphics (cs.SI).
